                            <comment id="10412" author="ludagoo" created="Tue, 26 Jan 2016 13:41:57 -0500"  >&lt;p&gt;interesting... several days ago I was working on adding some functionality to Prefect and initially tried to reference the current instance and got a compiler error (I do not remember what it was) so I fixed it by adding self. Which I think was a compiler suggestion... after seeing your comments i went and tried it again and can not get it to act up. weird.&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="10413" author="califrench" created="Tue, 26 Jan 2016 16:20:54 -0500"  >&lt;p&gt;For reference, the syntax to prevent a retain cycle in a closure when referencing &lt;tt&gt;self&lt;/tt&gt; is the following:&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;div class=&quot;code panel&quot; style=&quot;border-width: 1px;&quot;&gt;&lt;div class=&quot;codeContent panelContent&quot;&gt;
&lt;div class=&quot;error&quot;&gt;&lt;span class=&quot;error&quot;&gt;Unable to find source-code formatter for language: swift.&lt;/span&gt; Available languages are: actionscript, html, java, javascript, none, sql, xhtml, xml&lt;/div&gt;&lt;pre&gt;
dispatch_async(queue) { [weak self] in 
    print(self?.myInstanceVariableReference)
}
&lt;/pre&gt;
&lt;/div&gt;&lt;/div&gt;

&lt;p&gt;Note that self is an optional because it may have been de-allocated by the time the closure runs.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;Another option is to use &lt;tt&gt;unowned&lt;/tt&gt; like so:&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;div class=&quot;code panel&quot; style=&quot;border-width: 1px;&quot;&gt;&lt;div class=&quot;codeContent panelContent&quot;&gt;
&lt;div class=&quot;error&quot;&gt;&lt;span class=&quot;error&quot;&gt;Unable to find source-code formatter for language: swift.&lt;/span&gt; Available languages are: actionscript, html, java, javascript, none, sql, xhtml, xml&lt;/div&gt;&lt;pre&gt;
dispatch_async(queue) { [unowned self] in 
    print(self.myInstanceVariableReference)
}
&lt;/pre&gt;
&lt;/div&gt;&lt;/div&gt;

&lt;p&gt;But you may have a runtime error when self has been de-allocated, so the former is safer.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;Please see &lt;a href=&quot;http://stackoverflow.com/questions/24042949/block-retain-cycles-in-swift&quot; class=&quot;external-link&quot; rel=&quot;nofollow&quot;&gt;this Stack Overflow post&lt;/a&gt; for more information&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
